headline.print_headline: Georgian Own Goal Brings Relief to Strachan and Scotland
headline.main: Georgian Own Goal Brings Relief to Strachan and Scotland

lead_paragraph: Scotland dominated their Euro 2016 qualifier against Georgia but ultimately were grateful to settle for a 28th-minute own goal to gift them their first victory of the campaign at Ibrox on Saturday.
